    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> Do you suggest we automatically push it last in the list, or that we educate users into adding the widget last in their code?\n\nYes (I know it's kinda ugly :P)\n\n> I think the state->string and string->state logic should be in the helper, but the url synchronisation and load should be in the widget.\n\nI partially agree here. I think the helper should provide a way to get a meaningful subset of the state for serialization purpose, but not the serialization process itself. The serialization is part of the url mechanism as well. If we use other forms of storage, then the string wouldn't be meaningful but the sub object will always be.\n\nstate -> partial state + partial state -> state >> Helper\npartial state -> string vice versa, >> Widget\n",
